        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 5:45PM EDT by NWS Tampa Bay Ruskin FL</headline>
        <description>At 544 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Avon Park. This thunderstorm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Avon Park, Avon Park Executive Airport, and Frostproof.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
